"],"variants":[]},{"name":"Sutton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of numerous places called Sutton, named with Old English <i>sūth</i> ‘south, southern’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’. The English surname is also common in Ireland (Wexford, Kildare), where it has been established since the 13th century and Gaelicized as <b>de Sutún</b>.","Jewish (from the former Ottoman Empire, including Syria): unexplained.","English: topographic name from Middle English <i>(bi) suthentune</i> ‘(at the place to the) south of the village’."],"variants":[{"name":"Setton","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Avi, Ronit, Yossef.  French Andree, Henri, Jacques, Maryse.","Jewish (from the Ottoman Empire): altered form of   Sutton  .","English (Middlesex): variant of   Seaton  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mary of Sutton was born about 1100, in Sutton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Gilbert de Aston. She died in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1100–":"umbes 1100–Surnud","1100–1160":"1100–1160","1132–1195":"1132–1195","1100–Female":"1100–Surnud","Abt 1100":"umbes 1100","1100":"1100","1132":"1132","1195":"1195","about 1132":"umbes 1132","1160":"1160","Sutton, Cheshire, England":"Sutton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Runcorn, Cheshire, England":"Runcorn, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1100–":"noin 1100–Kuollut","1100–1160":"1100–1160","1132–1195":"1132–1195","1100–Female":"1100–Kuollut","Abt 1100":"noin 1100","1100":"1100","1132":"1132","1195":"1195","about 1132":"noin 1132","1160":"1160","Sutton, Cheshire, England":"Sutton, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Runcorn, Cheshire, England":"Runcorn, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1100–":"environ 1100–Décédée","1100–1160":"1100–1160","1132–1